IMO a big reason for why so many people got fascinated with Hogwarts is because the school was described as full of hidden halls, mysterious tunnels, secret rooms, hideouts etc. In real life people study in newly built boring buildings where there is nothing to explore/discover

My school was pretty old-ish and I've already told how much I loved to look for small spots: the hidden toilet behind the staircase wall, the secret locked mini-dungeon below the basement, mini rooftop rooms... these things do not exist in recently built buildings - sterility!
